    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1861-11-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1861-11-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="268" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d268">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Seward</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Pike</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 32.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of
                                    State</hi>,<lb/>
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1861-11-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 11, 1861</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your despatch of October 16 (No. 23) has
                            been received. It contains <pb facs="0387" n="387" xml:id="pg_387"/> the
                            reply of Mr. de Zuylen to the note you had addressed to him on the
                            subject of the “Sumter” at Paramaribo.</p>
                <p>In another paper I have already communicated the President’s views of the
                            disposition of that subject made by the government of the Netherlands,
                            so that nothing remains to be said on the subject which you have had
                            occasion to discuss in the despatch now before me.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
